core idea behind adding at a solution digit
digit is form of (acc, scratch, overflow, offset, do_add)

=== BEGIN INCREMENT ===

assumes pointing at do_add

set do_add
while do_add is true:
  reset do_add
  add 1 to acc
  set overflow
  subtract 10 from acc
  while acc is not zero:
    reset overflow
    move acc to scratch
    point to acc
  move scratch to acc
  add 10 to acc

  while overflow is true:
    reset overflow
    subtract 10 from acc
    move offset of this digit to offset of next digit
    point next digit
    increment offset of next digit
    set do_add on next digit
    point at overflow

  point at do_add

while offset is not zero:
  move offset to prev digit
  point prev digit
  decrement offset of prev digit

point at do_add
  

=== END INCREMENT ===  

  

=== BEGIN INCREMENT ===
+[
  -
  <<<<+
  >>+
  <<----------
  [
    >>-
    <<[>+<-]
  ]
  >[<+>-]
  <++++++++++>

  >[
    -
    <<---------->>
    >[<<<<<+>>>>>-]
    <<<<<
    +
    >+
    <<
  ]

  >>
]

<[
  [>>>>>+<<<<<-]
  >>>>>-
]

>
=== END INCREMENT ===
